## Fix Patterns

### Pattern A: Replace `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, X)` with `writer.WriteObjectValue(X, options)` 
This works for all local types implementing IJsonModel<T>. The `options` variable (ModelReaderWriterOptions) is always available in the enclosing method.

### Pattern B: Replace `JsonSerializer.Deserialize<T>(property.Value.GetRawText())` with static `T.DeserializeT(property.Value)`
All these local types have a static `DeserializeXxx(JsonElement element, ModelReaderWriterOptions options = null)` method. Since `property.Value` is already a `JsonElement`, pass it directly.

